owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: The application domain of the BMO is the bridge maintenance field. The BMO is designed to improve the management of maintenance knowledge of bridge lifecycle, and to provide more valuable information for bridge engineers to make holistic decisions.
owl:Ontology.owl:title: Bridge Maintenance Ontology (BMO)
owl:Ontology.Author: yali Jiang

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This bridge is a cable-stayed bridge with 540m (140m+260m+140m) long located in Dalian, Liaoning Province. Its main beam is connected with the pier and tower in the form of consolidation.
Measures, such as strengthening, replacement or adjustment of internal forces, need to be taken to make the bridge fit for use.
Functional, structural repair or replacement measures need to be taken to restore the bridge.
Reconstruction measures need to be taken to improve bridge technical standards, load levels, traffic capacity, disaster resistance, etc.
Measures need to be taken to repair slight damages.
Protective measures need to be taken to delay the degradation of structural performance and prolong the service life of the bridge.
